[normal]Why is this issue being discussed on 10/12/13, when the published deadline for the local consultation is 11/12/13? Will those who don't have time to respond until the last minute have their respo[bold]nses duly considered with equal weight to those submitted before papers were prepared for the policy board meeting scheduled on 10/12/13[bold]? [bold]Due to the new timetable this matter will now be dealt with by a Special Policy Board on 17[bold]th[bold] December. A number of ot[bold]her authorities are also holding additional Cabinet or Executive meetings to meet the timeframe[bold]Which working groups and scrutiny committees are dealing with this issue?[bold]None - due to the imposition of further consultation requirements there is insufficient[bold] time to refer this matter to a working group or for pre-scrutiny. There is however a Peoples Panel scheduled for 12[bold]th[bold] December[bold]Who are their members, and where can their minutes be found?[bold]N/a[bold]If there is no longer going to be a chief executive's post, who [bold]will take his place alongside the leader since[bold]"the Chief Executive be authorised, in consultation with the Leader, to agree the terms of any documentation required to enable the Authority to become a constituent authority of the Combined Authority includi[bold]ng the constitutional arrangements" (REPORT OF THE CHIEF EXECUTIVE[bold]Creation of a Combined Authority, presented to Policy Board 24/6/13) ?[bold]this will now fall to the Head of Paid Service Mr Steven Mason[bold].[bold]The agenda papers for the Policy Board meeting of 17 [bold]December will be available on the Council’s website from Tuesday, 10 December[bold].[bold]&#xa0;
